description:
ITV Tour de France 2016 Stage 2 PDTV x264-NX

3rd July 2016 ITV4
14:00 to 16:45 Stage 2

Gary Imlach and Chris Boardman present live coverage of stage 2 which starts at the departmental capital Saint-Lo, a town flattened during World War II and dubbed 'The Capital of the Ruins' by the playwright Samuel Beckett. The peloton heads north east across the Cherbourg Peninsula to the commercial, ferry and military port at Cherbourg-en-Cotentin on the English Channel. The final 1.9km of the stage ramp up to 6.5 per cent. Commentary by Ned Boulting and David Millar with Daniel Friebe reporting from the roadside.
